File is examples/community/latent_consistency_txt2img.py. It defines a pipeline for latent consistency model for text-to-image generation, using diffusers library. It includes a custom scheduler LCMScheduler, output class, pipeline class. Also helper functions betas_for_alpha_bar and rescale_zero_terminal_snr.

Thus summary: The module implements a latent consistency model pipeline for text-to-image generation, providing a custom diffusion scheduler (LCMScheduler) that extends DDPM with non‑Markovian guidance, an output container, and the pipeline class that orchestrates prompt encoding, latent preparation, model inference, safety checking, and returns generated images. It also includes utility functions for beta schedule and SNR rescaling.

Business intent: Provide an example implementation of a latent consistency diffusion pipeline that can be used by developers/researchers to generate images from text prompts, demonstrating integration with Hugging Face Diffusers and safety checking.
